83547def-6d04-450a-a72c-711f27be1459	The Valimail Team	team@valimail.com	Beyond DMARC - July 2025	If you haven’t joined already, there’s still until the end of the month left for our Engage-to-Enforce Challenge.\n\nWe’re celebrating ten years of Valimail this summer, and we started out to make email safer for everyone. A decade later, that mission is stronger than ever, thanks to you. Your feedback, your DNS tweaks, your drive to lock down DMARC policies: every action you take pushes the entire email ecosystem toward a more secure future.\n\nOver the past few weeks, we’ve had multiple domains achieve DMARC enforcement, and we’ve watched teams notch quick wins like fewer spoof attempts, clearer visibility, and a lot more peace of mind. To keep that momentum rolling, we’re sweetening the pot with fresh anniversary swag and up to 25% off Enforce and Amplify.\n\nWhether you’re publishing your very first DMARC record or tightening the screws on an existing deployment, there’s a next step waiting for you. Let’s make this final month count together.\nJoin the challenge today <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSI1H5n1kxJFS8AVk5WWbx_dqrN4RYmLahI8xBm0ZbB-EIfwtE0krWGgd8-SBBzg7S5w=>\nThree years running: Valimail remains #1 in G2 report for DMARC for the 12th consecutive quarter <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSFQy68rtzFPWomGnVHLKy1QHrOrAHYRgFNjbzbiS8qLv0y2Mf03tc-iqBdWwgGwjsDQ=>\nValimail marks 12 consecutive quarters as G2's top DMARC solution, showcasing our dedication to zero-trust email authentication.\nNew Zealand’s email security requirements and why they matter to all government domains <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSOyAMTJmz2Ap_9ScCabsatZsxo6K17gB_xjpbu2lRFGovoiKKcbdV3tDicdox75OZCU=>\nNew Zealand’s Secure Government Email (SGE) Framework mandates strict email authentication, highlighting the global importance of DMARC enforcement for government domains.\nAmazon SES and Valimail collaborate to help companies navigate b