e9ab4d79-9d68-4827-9a51-4b1acd9fba8f	The Valimail Team	team@valimail.com	Beyond DMARC - July 2025	If you haven’t joined already, there’s still until the end of the month left for our Engage-to-Enforce Challenge.\n\nWe’re celebrating ten years of Valimail this summer, and we started out to make email safer for everyone. A decade later, that mission is stronger than ever, thanks to you. Your feedback, your DNS tweaks, your drive to lock down DMARC policies: every action you take pushes the entire email ecosystem toward a more secure future.\n\nOver the past few weeks, we’ve had multiple domains achieve DMARC enforcement, and we’ve watched teams notch quick wins like fewer spoof attempts, clearer visibility, and a lot more peace of mind. To keep that momentum rolling, we’re sweetening the pot with fresh anniversary swag and up to 25% off Enforce and Amplify.\n\nWhether you’re publishing your very first DMARC record or tightening the screws on an existing deployment, there’s a next step waiting for you. Let’s make this final month count together.\nJoin the challenge today <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSI1H5n1kxJFS8AVk5WWbx_dqrN4RYmLahI8xBm0ZbB-EIfwtE0krWGgd8-SBBzg7S5w=>\nThree years running: Valimail remains #1 in G2 report for DMARC for the 12th consecutive quarter <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSFQy68rtzFPWomGnVHLKy1QHrOrAHYRgFNjbzbiS8qLv0y2Mf03tc-iqBdWwgGwjsDQ=>\nValimail marks 12 consecutive quarters as G2's top DMARC solution, showcasing our dedication to zero-trust email authentication.\nNew Zealand’s email security requirements and why they matter to all government domains <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSOyAMTJmz2Ap_9ScCabsatZsxo6K17gB_xjpbu2lRFGovoiKKcbdV3tDicdox75OZCU=>\nNew Zealand’s Secure Government Email (SGE) Framework mandates strict email authentication, highlighting the global importance of DMARC enforcement for government domains.\nAmazon SES and Valimail collaborate to help companies navigate bulk sender requirements <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSKiJxFp3_ZvgPo6t_fwMLowWQhaGGQbzV8V3KgB6PUa5rmJb_SKVEE1PxoHzlktMywo=>\nValimail and Amazon SES partner to streamline DMARC compliance, helping businesses meet bulk sender requirements and improve email deliverability.\nValimail Authenticated Answers with Tony Parrillo <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSNIwgwByINB2OZbbQOfpfb_ClYR4geLCtyaOyGCD5HE8s8nh0xKjyyluw4Xgn2pCdGw=>\nOur latest interview features Tony Parrillo, VP of Digital Engineering Global Cybersecurity at Schneider Electric, discussing leadership, risk management, and email security.\n- NCERT Warns of Cyber Threats from Email Misconfigurations (Do This ASAP) <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSFjcbGd2F1xKFNuRXklnkGG9rgdy5i5FjWlOLxu7LDhKxIukW7QwUn-DhlFigxqQ7EQ=> - The National Cyber Emergency Response Team (National CERT) has issued a fresh advisory highlighting cyber threats arising from email misconfigurations, urging both public and private sector organizations to take immediate security measures to protect against phishing, spoofing, and business email compromise attacks.\n\t- Detecting Deception: A CISO's Guide to Modern Threat Detection <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSJcqHkDvW40QI0smNe2KwgUvs7C8N81U0Ffj_6ocVwmzDCM5-kUbtsZLBB6e3Q6g0jg=> - In this essential episode of the KuppingerCole Analyst Chat, host Matthias Reinwarth welcomes cybersecurity strategist Jonathan Care to explore one of the most pressing challenges CISOs face in 2025: detecting deception in an age of AI-powered attacks.\n\t- GlobalSign Launches Verified Mark Certificates for Email Trust <https://get.valimail.com/OTM2LVNXRi05NzgAAAGblL1uSMwpsnDFkdDj_ywAd0I1VVMu1Xngco9qIT-gHr6OxD35p8RXasQk_Slv4FpNae4I0qI=> - GMO GlobalSign, a leading global Certificate Authority and digital identity solutions provider, has unveiled its Verified Mark Certificates (VMC) offering.\nNew and improved Valimail APIs\nWe recently released AP